#   DOC-001: rework all INDEX.md to the meta/index.mkd format

Rework every production-module-dir `INDEX.md` to match [index]: a top intro,
then ONE SECTION PER `.h` file — each a short mission intro + a ≤12-bullet list
of the module's KEY types/functions (one-liner each), sections grouped by
layer/theme. Explanatory tables/drawings move OUT of the INDEX into per-file
`.md` docs (e.g. `abc/S.md`), linked from the section intro; those `.md` docs
are created/expanded as part of this work. Docs-only, but every entry must be
verified against the real header. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Current INDEX.md files are flat module tables (e.g. `abc/INDEX.md` is a
    `| Header | Description |` table, module-level only, no per-entry detail) —
    not the [index] format.
 -  [index] (settled 2026-06-16): intro (≤8 lines) → a SECTION PER `.h` file:
    module intro (≤4 lines, the mission) + a bullet list of KEY entries
    (types/functions), one-liner each (≤2 lines), MAX 12 bullets per module.
    Template headers list the `*`-form (e.g. `*csMv`), not each instantiation.
 -  Q&A decisions (2026-06-16): section PER `.h` FILE (companions NOT grouped);
    inline explanatory tables/diagrams (e.g. abc boundary-movers) MOVE to per-file
    `.md` docs and link from the section intro; DOC-001 ALSO creates/expands those
    `.md` docs; sections GROUPED BY LAYER/THEME (foundation→containers→io/net→app).

### Goals
 -  Every production module dir with public API has an `INDEX.md` in [index] form:
    intro + layer-grouped per-`.h` sections, each mission + ≤12 key type/function
    one-liners, accurate to the header.
 -  Explanatory prose/tables/diagrams live in per-file `.md` docs (created/expanded
    here), linked from the section intro; the INDEX stays intro + sections + bullets.

### Constraints
 -  Scope = production module dirs (+ API subdirs): abc, dog (+git, +tok), keeper,
    graf, sniff, spot, bro, woof, mark, js, beagle. SKIP pure test/fuzz fixture dirs.
 -  Line budget ([index]): top intro 8, section intro 4, bullet 2, nested 1; ≤12
    bullets/module. Verify every entry against the real header — no invented APIs.
 -  abc/ is core: its INDEX + `.md` docs gate for review (docs-only, still surface).

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  Per-dir parallel execution (like the CODE/PTR sweeps): one worktree per dir,
    ~6 at once; abc is the largest (~70 headers → ~70 sections).
 -  Pick the ≤12 "key" entries per module by reading the header for its entry-point
    types/functions; the rest stays in the header (the INDEX is leads, not a dump).

### TODOs
-[ ] Per dir: rewrite `INDEX.md` to intro + layer-grouped per-`.h` sections
      (mission + ≤12 key entries); move tables/diagrams to per-file `.md`, link them.
-[ ] Create/expand the per-file `.md` docs that receive moved content.
-[ ] Verify every entry against its header; hold the [index] line budget.
-[ ] (abc) gate the diff for review; land the rest per [Issues].

### Blockers and bummers
 -  Big-dir effort (abc ~70 sections) — parallelize per dir; ≤12/module is the cap
    that keeps any one INDEX from ballooning.

##  Outcome
 -  *LANDED 2026-06-17.* All 11 production-dir `INDEX.md` reworked to the [index]
    format (intro + per-`.h` sections, ≤12 key one-liner entries, layer-grouped) and
    UNWRAPPED to one greppable physical line per block within the codepoint budget
    (head 64 / bullet 128 / section-intro 256 / top-intro 512), verified by the `mark`
    linter. Commits: 10 parent dirs `8bd51f9b`, parent abc-pin `1a5d0cbf`, abc sub
    `4222dfab` (on synthetic branch `?/abc/.dogs`). abc gate: reviewed, zero symbols
    dropped; glosses corrected (the failed run's `*Z`-as-"sentinel" is now the `a<b`
    comparator). DESCOPED (user decision "trim to fit"): the per-file `.md` docs that
    would HOLD moved detail were NOT created — over-budget bullets were trimmed to
    terse leads instead (heaviest loss in the prose `.c`-unit sections of woof/mark/
    beagle). A future ticket can relocate that detail into `*.md` docs.
 -  *CALIBRATION FAILED 2026-06-16 (abc, discarded).* A single-pass worker reworked
    `abc/INDEX.md` to the format (9 layers, 60 per-`.h` sections, 104→446 lines) but the
    quality was BS: (1) entries crammed 4-6 symbols per bullet with a 2-3-word CATEGORY
    label → unreadable (couldn't tell what any one symbol does); (2) the glosses were
    FACTUALLY WRONG — e.g. `wh128Z`/`u*Z` described as a "sentinel" when it is the ordering
    COMPARATOR (`a<b`); the worker pattern-matched names instead of reading bodies. Its
    "verified every entry" only checked that NAMES EXIST, not that descriptions are correct.
    LESSON: an LLM writing per-symbol glosses from header NAMES hallucinates meanings. Any
    redo MUST (a) derive each gloss from the symbol's actual DEFINITION (signature + body),
    one symbol (or tight pair) per line with a plain "what it does" gloss, genuinely
    SELECTIVE (the ~12 leads, not all-compressed), and (b) run an INDEPENDENT adversarial
    verify pass that re-reads each symbol's definition and refutes/fixes any gloss that
    doesn't match the code — name-existence checking is NOT enough. Otherwise: defer (a dull
    flat index beats a wrong one).

